\fs28\b 4. Scientific Backing Requirements for Soil Restoration Claims\b0\fs24\par
\par
\fs26\b Measurement and Quantification Standards\b0\fs24\par
\par
\b Core Requirements:\b0\par
\bullet Robust quantification based on conservative approaches, completeness, and scientific methods\par
\bullet Empirical crediting based directly on soil sampling with highest possible quality\par
\bullet Ground-based measurements foundational to high-integrity carbon credits\par
\bullet Regional baselines and methodologies for improved measurement and accounting\par
\par
\b Verification Framework:\b0\par
\bullet GHG emission reductions/removals must be real, measurable, additional, permanent, independently verified, conservatively estimated, uniquely numbered, and transparently listed\par
\bullet Projects must ensure carbon stays stored for decades, protecting against reversals from fire, disease, or changing practices\par
\bullet Additionality requirement: verified credits must result from activities beyond business-as-usual\par
\par
\b Technology Integration Requirements:\b0\par
\bullet Satellite imaging and machine learning integration\par
\bullet Robust monitoring methodologies\par
\bullet Regional models for better accuracy of net GHG mitigation estimates\par
\bullet Complete accounting including nitrous oxide for overall climate impact assessment\par
